Two Chinese businessmen were robbed while travelling from Ladysmith to Durban early this morning. While on the R103 near Frere, Estcourt their vehicle was followed by a black Mercedes Benz with no registration plates. The four occupants of the vehicle ordered them to take the Frere Road turn-off, and fired four gun shots into the driver s door. One of the bullets struck the 41 year old driver in the leg. The vehicle was stopped and it is reported that the four suspects stole around R30 000 cash from the vehicle. The Chinese nationals managed to drive back to Ladysmith where they sought medical attention at a local hospital. A case of robbery and attempted murder is being investigated by Estcourt police.